race.comment: TUSSOCK (6) ran a bold race over this journey last time, leading for much of the way before fading out of it late to finish 3.5 lengths away in fourth at Manangatang. Will take catching. FINAL QUARTER (10) made progress last time out, finishing 2.5 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1550m at Manangatang. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. BO COUGAR (5) finished third last time over 2000m at Manangatang, beaten 2.5 lengths. In the right race and is a key runner. MASTER POLANSKI (1) is experiencing a long win drought, extended last start when fifth over 1856m at Kyneton after being prominent at the corner. Placed to advantage and can make amends.
